eight: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The post i found this on had 25,000 upvotes, if this gets at least 69 i'd be nice</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/a7eiXST</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[StormCrowMith]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My sister died today</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9i1b2fD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wGRnVaf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My sister died today. I love her so much and I’m the only friend she really had in life. I feel so heartbroken that she suffered so much in her 33 years on this earth. I can only hope she has peace now and that she knew how much I love her. Her name is Chelsey. Please send her some love.                         -edit- I posted this because she was very alone in the world and I want people to think of her with care, in a way she deserved but rarely got. She had the biggest heart of anyone and suffered so much because of it. Thank you to everyone who said her name or held her in your thoughts, that’s all I can do for her now. She loved kitties and rubber duckies and cooking. If you want to donate in her name, an animal charity, a rehab facility, an organization that fights homelessness, or helps battered women would be good as those all describe her life. She was very silly and had a great sense of humor. She touched the people who she came in contact with. I hope for a few days her spirit lives on through all of you because god damn it life isn’t fair and she deserves better than this.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9i1b2fD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[midlifecrisisapproaching]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Very true...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/wo5eCIC</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GJUSz72.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.co